cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.SI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on extracting templates from phrases. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper presents an unsupervised approach for template extraction using a novel variant of the Sequence Binary Decision Diagram. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with automated extraction of templates from text. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible category as the paper deals with extracting templates from corpora and short messages from social media. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also a possible category as the paper deals with extracting templates from short messages from social media.
